          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "High-pressure gas-bottles filled with mixtures of",
                "enriched 22Ne and CH4 were used. Two samples were",
                "prepared. Sphere #1 contained 75.1 mg methane and",
                "352.41 mg 22Ne, while sphere #2 was filled with 19.7",
                "mg methane and 129.57 mg 22Ne. The masses of the",
                "2-cm- diameter stainless steel containers were about",
                "8600 mg. An additional larger aluminum sphere 80 mm",
                "in diameter with Ne was used for measuring the 22Ne",
                "capture gamma-rays by means of the invisible",
                "container concept."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "cold neutron beam with an approximately Maxwellian",
                "energy distribution of 100 K. In the 80 mm-sphere",
                "experiment, the flux was 3xl0**7 n/s/cm2, while for",
                "the 2 cm containers  (sphere #1 and #2) it was",
                "7xl0**7 n/s/cm2 at the sample position."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The de-exciting gamma-rays were measured with",
                "a BGO shielded HPGe detector and the spectra were",
                "collected in a 16K MCA system."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The cross section was determined by means of the",
                "comparator method, and an improved decay-scheme",
                "obtained in the work. The thermal equivalent cross",
                "section value is based on the assumption that both of",
                "the comparator (hydrogen) and 22Ne have 1/v cross",
                "sections for the whole beam energy range."
              ]
            }
          ],
